ia-labelledby="mceu_32" role="button" aria-label="Increase indent" aria-disabled="false"><button role="presentation" type="button" tabindex="-1"><i class="mce-ico mce-i-indent"></i></button></div><div id="mceu_33" class="mce-widget mce-btn mce-disabled" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="mceu_33" role="button" aria-label="Undo" aria-disabled="true"><button role="presentation" type="button" tabindex="-1"><i class="mce-ico mce-i-undo"></i></button></div><div id="mceu_34" class="mce-widget mce-btn mce-disabled" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="mceu_34" role="button" aria-label="Redo" aria-disabled="true"><button role="presentation" type="button" tabindex="-1"><i class="mce-ico mce-i-redo"></i></button></div><div id="mceu_35" class="mce-widget mce-btn mce-last" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="mceu_35" role="button" aria-label="Keyboard Shortcuts"><button role="presentation" type="button" tabindex="-1"><i class="mce-ico mce-i-wp_help"></i></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id="mceu_42" class="mce-edit-area mce-container mce-panel mce-stack-layout-item" hidefocus="1" tabindex="-1" role="group" style="border-width: 1px 0px 0px;"><iframe id="post_content_ifr" frameborder="0" allowtransparency="true" title="Rich Text Area. Press Alt-Shift-H for help" src='javascript:""' style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block;"></iframe></div><div id="mceu_43" class="mce-statusbar mce-container mce-panel mce-last mce-stack-layout-item" hidefocus="1" tabindex="-1" role="group" style="border-width: 1px 0px 0px;"><div id="mceu_43-body" class="mce-container-body mce-flow-layout"><div id="mceu_44" class="mce-path mce-first mce-flow-layout-item"><div role="button" class="mce-path-item mce-last" data-index="0" tabindex="-1" id="mceu_44-0" aria-level="0">p</div></div><div id="mceu_45" class="mce-last mce-flow-layout-item mce-resizehandle"><i class="mce-ico mce-i-resize"></i></div></div></div></div></div><textarea class="required wp-editor-area" rows="10" autocomplete="off" cols="40" name="post_content" id="post_content" style="display: none;" aria-hidden="true">&lt;p&gt;System test only&lt;br /&gt;
Our client is a well established custom machine shop with state of the art technology and an impressive customer base.&nbsp; They have a stable history of growth and have established a culture of continuous improvement that has helped maintain their niche leadership position year after year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Located a short 20 minute drive outside&nbsp;the city, the commute is against the flow of traffic and the cost of living in a smaller community is attractive also.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a good opportunity to demonstrate leadership qualities and advance your career. Candidates with solid technical skills may grow into the leadership role over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Lead the CNC programming group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The incumbent will interpret customer drawings and process requirements from documents and communications with project managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities include generating accurate process drawings, tool-sheets, and CNC code using relevant software, design fixtures and clamping methods, utilising the best cutting tools and processes working with tool suppliers, ensuring that all lead times are achieved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Continuous improvement is a daily event in all the tasks performed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to conduct regular performance reviews with the CNC programming team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="job_req"&gt;
&lt;div class="RichText_Content"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position requires&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of 5 years CNC milling programming experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with GIBBS and Mastercam an asset, training is available if necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of 5 axis simultaneously programming&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advance knowledge of cutting tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced knowledge of machining a wide variety of materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to quality and strong attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced understanding of engineering drawings with ability to Interpret Geometric Tolerances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work in a team environment, with minimal supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of self-motivation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dependability and reliable personal transportation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3 class="h2"&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p align="justify"&gt;The Executive Wing is an Executive Search Firm whose principals are comprised of senior headhunters with a business philosophy in sync with today's economic realities. Founded and incorporated in 2008 in London, Ontario we are a unique, market driven organization with a corporate mission we all embrace: The Executive Wing will be Canada's most innovative and respected executive search firm by providing superior service, results and value to our clients and candidates. Our Principals have successfully completed over 2000 client searches including international searches in the U.S., Europe, and Mexico. Since 1986, The Executive Wing’s Principals have consistently raised the bar in executive search by identifying the highest caliber of talent in the marketplace - talent that meets the unique cultural needs and business goals of our clients. As a networked firm, we combine the critical benefits of global reach, local savvy and breadth and depth of industry expertise. We perform each search with a commitment to excellence and to the development of long-term client relationships. As a result, more than 70% of our firm's business is realized with existing clients who have regularly renewed their confidence in The Executive Wing.&lt;/p&gt;
